Job Summary 
 
We are looking to hire a Request for Proposal Specialist to join our Institutional Asset Management team. In this role, you will be responsible for all phases of the proposal process for RFPs, DDQs and Questionnaires. This role is responsible for researching, writing, editing, reviewing and producing proposals as well as responding to due diligence 
 
This is a unique opportunity to support new business acquisition and help retain existing clients, while partnering with investment research, sales and business development teams, and legal/compliance. 
 
The ideal candidate is ideally someone who is collaborative, autonomous, and detail oriented. Weâ€™re also looking for someone who is energized by building and structuring the RFP process from the ground up. 
 
Key Responsibilities 
 
 Owning and optimizing RFPs, DDQs and Questionnaires along the investment management sales lifecycle. 
 Project manage the proposal process from qualification to completion and delivery. 
 Lead communication of proposals, DDQs and RFIs, including scheduling vetting calls and delivering timelines with a list of action items to all stakeholders. 
 Research, write, and edit accurate, compelling and client-focused responses to RFPs, RFIs, and due diligence requests 
 Produce effective and compelling representations of data and analysis for targeted content which optimizes client and prospect communication 
 Implement and manage an RFP Response Platform (we currently use Salesforce) 
 Requirements 
 5+ years directly related work experience in an Investment Management firm, consulting firm, pension plan, institutional sales team, or equivalent 
 Strong project management skills with high attention to detail 
 Excellent writing skills with experience completing RFIs/RFPs/DDQs 
 Strong client management skills 
 Prior experience working with third party databases, tools, and technologies like Salesforce 
 Ability to juggle and prioritize multiple projects simultaneously 
 
